					Repo layout, build (CMake), CI (format, lint, tests), sanitizers on Debug.

					Logger stub, error types, basic ConfigModel.

		Phase 1 – Config (2–3 days)

					Lexer+parser → AST → Model; validation & helpful errors.

					Unit tests for directives and failure cases.

		Phase 2 – Networking core (2–3 days)

					EventLoop + poll(); Listener & Connection.

					Echo server integration test; timers.

		Phase 3 – HTTP parser & response (3–4 days)

					Incremental parser; minimal responder (200/404) from a single root.

					Keep-alive + timeouts. Unit + integration tests.

		Phase 4 – Routing & virtual servers (2–3 days)

					Host & location match; method allowlist; redirects.

					Tests: precedence matrix.

		Phase 5 – Static files & autoindex (2–3 days)

					Index selection, mime types, autoindex.

					Tests: traversal protection, symlink policy.

		Phase 6 – Uploads & DELETE (3–4 days)

					multipart/form-data parser, upload_store, size limits.

					DELETE handler with guardrails.

		Phase 7 – CGI (4–6 days)

					Env builder, fork/execve, pipes, header parsing, timeouts, kill tree.

					Tests: happy path, bad script, infinite loop, huge output.

		Phase 8 – Hardening & polish (2–4 days)

					Error pages, access logs, metrics, graceful shutdown.

					Benchmark & regressions.

		Bonus Phase – Advanced (as time permits)

					Swap poll() → epoll/kqueue.

					Chunked transfer.

					ETag/Last-Modified; range requests.

					Hot reload (SIGHUP) if permitted.

